      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "9e860054b8a6cca4d0f4addc075a0533b49b8441",
            "subject": "LU-15885 o2iblnd: fix handling of RDMA_CM_EVENT_UNREACHABLE"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Serguei Smirnov",
          "email": "ssmirnov@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2023-11-30 18:55:11.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Etienne AUJAMES",
          "email": "etienne.aujames@cea.fr",
          "date": "2024-09-27 16:38:53.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-17325 o2iblnd: CM_EVENT_UNREACHABLE on established conn",
        "message": "LU-17325 o2iblnd: CM_EVENT_UNREACHABLE on established conn\n\nThere were examples in the field with RoCE setups which demonstrate\nthat CM_EVENT_UNREACHABLE may be received when connection is already\nin ESTABLISHED state. This causes an assert in kiblnd_cm_callback to\nfail.\n\nHandle this in a more gracious manner: report the event as unexpected\nand allow the flow to continue. If there are indeed issues on\nthe connection, it is expected to report transaction errors later\nand get cleaned up without crashing the whole system.\n\nLustre-change: https://review.whamcloud.com/53298\nLustre-commit: f7051f0092b19416ed86d7f4bbfe1cba7bb74c02\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-lnet\nSigned-off-by: Serguei Smirnov <ssmirnov@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: If32166fe9fc59e025609c2035cb1c03d3bed22f2\nReviewed-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Frank Sehr <fsehr@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Cyril Bordage <cbordage@whamcloud.com>\nSigned-off-by: Etienne AUJAMES <eaujames@ddn.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_15"
    }
  },
